  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Major depressive episode; inpatient at screening visit; suicidal ideation/behaviour
             present defined by a clinical rating of 8 on the Sheehan Suicidality Tracking Scale
             (S-STS) and a rating of ≥20 on the Montgomery Asberg Depression Scale (MADRS) at both
             screening and baseline visits; both gender, age 18 years.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contraindication for and history of lithium treatment within the past 6 months;
             patient unable to tolerate lithium treatment in the past; comorbid
             borderline/antisocial personality disorder, currently active substance dependency;
             patients with acute or unstable severe medical conditions, patients unable to
             understand the informed consent or involuntary inpatients, positive toxicology screen
             (illegal drugs), pregnancy and lactation
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
